#CHIP NES
#CLOCK 1789773

; NES APU Noise Channel Test
;
; The NES has one noise channel that generates pseudo-random noise for:
; - Percussion sounds (drums, cymbals)
; - Bass effects
; - Atmospheric textures
;
; Features:
; - LFSR (Linear Feedback Shift Register) modes
; - Pitch control (via loop counter)
; - Volume envelope
;
; Tests:
; - Different LFSR modes
; - Noise pitch variations
; - Volume control

#TRACK 0

TEMPO 120

; Noise drum pattern (periodic noise hits)
n4 . . n4 . . n4 . .

r4

; Noise with pitch variation
n8 n8 n8 n8 n8 n8 n8 n8

r4

; Sustained noise (cymbal-like)
n2 . .

r4

; Complex noise rhythm
n4 . n16 n16 n16 n16 n4 .

r2

#END
